-- O2 Czech Republic shares fall after shareholder asks for loan
-- By Jason Hovet
-- Wed Oct 15, 2014 03:26AM EDT
-- None



PRAGUE, Oct 15 (Reuters) - Shares in Czech telecoms operator O2 Czech Republic <SPTT.PR> fell in early trading on Wednesday after the company said its majority shareholder had asked for a loan of up to 24.8 billion crowns ($1.14 billion).

Shares traded down 7.4 percent at 273 crowns at 0712 GMT. The company said in a statement late on Tuesday that shareholder PPF had requested the loan to pay off part of an acquisition bank loan. [ID:nL6N0S958R]